{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1671\cocoasubrtf600 {\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Bold;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red71\green91\blue98;\red83\green104\blue112;} {\*\expandedcolortbl;;\csgenericrgb\c27843\c35686\c38431;\csgenericrgb\c32549\c40784\c43922;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 Demo Receiver: \f1\b0 \cf3 The MiniTioune/MiniTiouner[-Express] system uses an ASIC chip to take a DVB-S or DVB-S2 signal all the way through demodulation and decoding. These ASICs are designed to handle the symbol rates used in commercial broadcast. \ \ The module inside the MiniTiouner is called a NIM, or network interface module, and often referred to as a \'93tuner\'94, but it is also a demodulator and a decoder. It takes the signal all the way down to an MPEG Transport Stream. \ \ Short data sheet on one of the NIM models used with MiniTioune: \ \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wiki.batc.org.uk/images/4/46/FTS-4335_Series_F2.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 https://wiki.batc.org.uk/images/4/46/FTS-4335_Series_F2.pdf}}\ \ Data brief for the demodulator/decoder device in the 4335 NIM: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://datasheet.octopart.com/STV0910ADB-STMicroelectronics-datasheet-16349956.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 https://datasheet.octopart.com/STV0910ADB-STMicroelectronics-datasheet-16349956.pdf}}\ \ While the transmitter can produce a variety of transport streams, and the deployed beacon will use both Generic Stream Encapsulation and MPEG transport streams, the demonstration receiver can only receive MPEG transport streams. }
